'''Aiy''' ([[Sakha language|Sakha]]: ''Айыы'', [[Russian language|Russian]]: ''Айыы'') are benevolent spirits in [[Yakuts]] [[mythology]]. They are creators of the world and of the fabulous land of the Yakut Olonkhos. In Sakha belief, creator of the world "Urung Ai Toyon", is the greatest of them.<ref>Türk Mitolojisi Ansiklopedik Sözlük, Celal Beydili, Yurt Yayınevi {{tr icon}}</ref> According to mythology, the Aiy live in the Upper World. It is believed that the Aiy will not accept blood [[sacrifice]] and therefore they are presented "victims" of [[vegetable]] and [[dairy product]]s.
Aiy symbols are required for the ''Ysyakh'' (spring feast) and regulated by the government of the [[Sakha Republic]].<ref>ПРАВИТЕЛЬСТВО РЕСПУБЛИКИ САХА (ЯКУТИЯ). ПОСТАНОВЛЕНИЕ от 3 июня 2009 г. № 241 [http://yakutialaw.ru/2009-god/postanovlenie-ot-3-iyunya-2009-g.-n-241.html] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305003757/http://yakutialaw.ru/2009-god/postanovlenie-ot-3-iyunya-2009-g.-n-241.html |date=2016-03-05 }} {{ru icon}}</ref>
