{{short description|20th-century Catholic Archbishop of Villavicencio}} {{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | name = Gregorio Garavito Jiménez, S.M.M. | title = [[Archbishop of Catholic Archdiocese of Villavicencio|Archiocese of Villavicencio]] | image = | alt = | caption = | church = [[Catholic Church]] | archdiocese = | diocese = | see = [[Catholic Archdiocese of Villavicencio|Archiocese of Villavicencio]] | term = 1969–1994 | predecessor = Frans Joseph Bruls Canisius | successor = Alfonso Cabezas Aristizábal <!-- Orders --> | ordination = July 24, 1942 | ordinated_by = | consecration = | consecrated_by = | rank = <!-- Personal details --> | birth_date = {{birth date|1919|3|9}} | birth_place = [[Junín, Cundinamarca|Junín, Colombia]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2016|2|16|1919|3|9}} | death_place = | previous_post = Priest }}
'''Gregorio Garavito Jiménez''' S.M.M. (March 9, 1919&nbsp;– February 16, 2016) was a Colombian [[bishop]] of the [[Catholic Church]]. At the time of his death, he was one of oldest Colombian Catholic bishops.
Garavito was born in [[Junín, Cundinamarca|Junín, Colombia]] and was ordained a priest on July 24, 1942, from the religious order of [[Louis de Montfort|Missionaries of the Company of Mary]]. Monsignor Garavito was appointed auxiliary bishop of the [[Catholic Archdiocese of Villavicencio|Archiocese of Villavicencio]] as well as titular bishop of Cyparissia on December 4, 1961, and consecrated on February 11, 1962. He was appointed archbishop of the [[Catholic Archdiocese of Villavicencio|Archiocese of Villavicencio]] on April 26, 1969, and retired on May 3, 1994.
